    dc:title "Small snails in a big place: a radiation in the semi-arid rangelands in northern Australia (Eupulmonata, Camaenidae, Nanotrachia gen. nov.)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890441>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890443>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890447>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890449> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890441>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Shells of Nanotrachia species studied herein. A, N. intermedia (Solem, 1984) (paratype AM C.146110); B, Nanotrachia carinata sp. nov. (paratype WAM S49100); C, N. coronata sp. nov. (paratype WAM S49086); D, N. costulata costulata sp. nov. (WAM S49088); E, N. levis sp. nov. (paratype WAM S49096); F, N. orientalis (Solem, 1984) (paratype AM C.146105); G, Mouldingia occidentalis (Solem, 1984) (paratype AM C.146107). Scale bar = 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4890441/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890443>
    dc:description "Figure 5. SEM micrographs of shells showing protoconch and teleoconch microsculpture. A–B, N. carinata sp. nov. (paratype WAM S49100); C–D, N. coronata sp. nov. (paratype WAM S49086); E–F, Nanotrachia costulata sp. nov. (WAM S49088); G–H, N. levis sp. nov. (paratype WAM S49096). Scale bars: A, C, E, G = 1 mm; B, D, F, H = 200 Mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4890443/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890447>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Penial anatomy. A, Nanotrachia intermedia (Solem, 1984) (WAM S49195); B, N. intermedia (Solem, 1984) (WAM S49194); C, Nanotrachia carinata sp. nov. (holotype WAM S66300); D, N. levis sp. nov. (holotype WAM S6630). Insets showing schematic cross section of mid-penis. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4890447/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890449>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Intraspecific variation of penial anatomy in N. costulata sp. nov. A, Nanotrachia c. costulata (holotype WAM S66302); B, Nanotrachia c. costulata (WAM S49174); C, Nanotrachia c. montejinni ssp. nov. (holotype NTM P48939); D, Nanotrachia c. montejinni (AM C.437659). Insets showing schematic cross section of midpenis. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4890449/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

